Kilimanjaro National Park is in Tanzania, the eastern part of Africa.
It is famous for its mountain.
Mt. Kilimanjaro is higher than Mt. Fuji.
It is 5,895 meters high.
The climate of Mt. Kilimanjaro is different from place to place.
At the foot of the mountain, the savanna spreads out, and it is hot.
The top of the mountain is much colder than the foot of the mountain.
The temperature is always below zero.
Glaciers over the top all year round.
How high is Mt. Kilimanjaro?
